abstract: Jane D. Hartley, chief executive officer of an economic consulting firm, will serve in France, and Kevin F. O’Malley, a lawyer, will fill a long-vacant post in Ireland.
snippet: Jane D. Hartley, chief executive officer of an economic consulting firm, will serve in France, and Kevin F. O’Malley, a lawyer, will fill a long-vacant post in Ireland.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Obama on Friday nominated Jane D. Hartley, the chief executive officer of an economic consulting firm, to be ambassador to France, once more propelling a campaign fund-raiser into a prominent diplomatic position.

abstract: While AT&T’s bid for DirecTV bears similarity to Comcast’s deal for Time Warner Cable, experts say the differences could lead regulators to separate conclusions for each one.
snippet: While AT&T’s bid for DirecTV bears similarity to Comcast’s deal for Time Warner Cable, experts say the differences could lead regulators to separate conclusions for each one.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Many supporters of the blockbuster Comcast-Time Warner Cable merger breathed a sigh of relief on Sunday, when AT&T and DirecTV announced plans to merge, thinking the latest pairing would divert some regulatory scrutiny of the other high-stakes deal.

abstract: A nomination of Hillary Rodham Clinton for president would likely block the paths for other women running for the White House, and for those who would like to be vice president.
snippet: A nomination of Hillary Rodham Clinton for president would likely block the paths for other women running for the White House, and for those who would like to be vice president.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Few doubt that Hillary Rodham Clinton’s nomination for president would be good for women. But her candidacy would also probably block the paths for other women running for the White House, and, notably, for those who would like to be vice president.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — As the high-profile congressional fight over military sexual assault recedes, lawmakers are broadening their focus to an array of sex crimes like college campus assaults, preying on child and human trafficking.

abstract: Female politicians make dismissive words work for them.
snippet: Female politicians make dismissive words work for them.
lead_paragraph: AMES, Iowa — “UNBECOMING.” “Miss Congeniality.” Not sufficiently “ladylike.” In politics, these words and phrases have long been used to belittle female candidates. But now, female politicians are increasingly trying to rethink — and reclaim — how language shapes how they are perceived.

abstract: A group of senators from both parties hope debate on a bipartisan child care bill can end months of political gridlock.
snippet: A group of senators from both parties hope debate on a bipartisan child care bill can end months of political gridlock.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — It says something about the current gridlock of Congress that the small deal the Senate will consider this week could be kind of big.

abstract: On the national level, the Democratic bench is weaker than at any time in the past several decades.
snippet: On the national level, the Democratic bench is weaker than at any time in the past several decades.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — If Hillary Rodham Clinton doesn’t run for the Democratic presidential nomination in 2016 — and there’s one chance in five of that — the party could have a nervous breakdown.
